The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 April is 41,549 (4,809 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 April, there were 129 new confirmed cases (14.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 31 March, there were 184 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 30% (55 fewer cases).
